# Conventional Commits

All commits use **Conventional Commits** enforced by Commitlint.

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

- **type** (required): `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`
- **scope** (optional): short area, e.g. `auth`, `ui`, `deps`
- **description** (required): imperative mood, lowercase, no period at end — e.g. `add login form`, not `Added login form.`

## Examples

```
feat(ui): add primary button variants
fix(router): correct lazy route path for dashboard
chore(deps): bump angular to 19.x
docs(readme): document nvm and format scripts
```

## Anti-patterns

- `WIP`, `fix stuff`, or vague one-word subjects
- Subject line ending with `.`
- Type not in the allowed list (see `commitlint.config.cjs`)

When suggesting a commit message for the user, output a **single line** matching the format above.
